        <section class="technical-details">
            <h3>Architecture</h3>
            <p>The system is a small static site with optional Vercel serverless endpoints for GitHub OAuth. Pages are plain HTML that reuse a shared stylesheet and a small client script at <code>assets/app.js</code>.</p>


            

            <h3>Implementation Notes</h3>
            <p>Keep shared styles in <code>assets/style.css</code> and reuse the same header/footer markup for a consistent site layout. The OAuth endpoints are in <code>api/auth/</code> and require Vercel environment variables:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>GITHUB_CLIENT_ID</code></li>
                <li><code>GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET</code></li>
                <li>Set these in the Vercel dashboard for the project before deploying.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
